DataElement.preferredDefinition: An indication as to whether the patient meets the eligibility requirements for participation in a clinical trial with regards to the assessments for high suspicion of cancer.

ReferenceDocuments.name: High suspicion of ovarian can
ReferenceDocuments.description: High suspicion of ovarian cancer, pancreatic cancer, kidney cancer, or melanoma by clinical and/or radiological assessment, with plans for histologic or cytologic confirmation within 28 days after study blood draw

ReferenceDocuments.name: NRG CRF Text 1
ReferenceDocuments.description: Does the patient have radiographically suspicious ipsilateral or contralateral axillary, supraclavicular, infraclavicular, or internal mammary lymph nodes, unless there is histological confirmation that these nodes are negative for metastatic disease?
